Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine), metabolic acidosis (low CO₂), and marked proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, suggesting possible diabetic nephropathy or another renal pathology despite low HbA1c. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity) further support renal dysfunction. No evidence of urinary infection. Clinical correlation and nephrology evaluation are recommended.
